results.report_summary: The report discusses how autonomous agents utilize external memory retrieval through Maximum Inner Product Search (MIPS) and the necessity of Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) methods in this context. It provides an overview of key ANN algorithms including Locality-Sensitive Hashing (LSH), ANNOY, Hierarchical Navigable Small World (HNSW), Facebook AI Similarity Search (FAISS), and ScaNN, each briefly described. The report concludes with an explanation of the trade-off between latency and recall in these systems, highlighting the balance required for efficient and accurate vector search in high-dimensional spaces.
